# *Nominal Categories*

- Because these variablesâ€™ categories have no ordering or numeric equivalents, itâ€™s impossible to calculate a mean or median, percentiles, ranges, â€¦

â†’ It is possible to calculate the **mode** - the most common value in the data set.

- TheÂ `.value_counts()`Â function calculates the count of each value in a column and returns the result as a series.
- By default,Â `.value_counts()`Â orders categories in descending order by frequency, thus the top row in the output will be the mode.

```sql
counts = df['marital.status'].value_counts()
print(counts)
```

- We can also extract the name of the modal category by taking the first value from the seriesÂ `.value_counts()`Â returns.

```sql
modal_cat = counts.index[0]
print(modal_cat) # Output: Married-civ-spouse
```

